{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id05844ae3-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1677d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1677d"},"text":"§ 1677d.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Countervailable subsidy practices discovered during a proceeding","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"chapeau","attrib":{},"text":"If, in the course of a proceeding under this subtitle, the administering authority discovers a practice which appears to be a countervailable subsidy, but was not included in the matters alleged in a countervailing duty petition, or if the administering authority receives notice from the Trade Representative that a subsidy or subsidy program is in violation of Article 8 of the Subsidies Agreement, then the administering authority—","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05844ae4-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1677d/1"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1"},"text":"(1)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shall include the practice, subsidy, or subsidy program in the proceeding if the practice, subsidy, or subsidy program appears to be a countervailable subsidy with respect to the merchandise which is the subject of the proceeding, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"paragraph","attrib":{"id":"id05844ae5-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d","identifier":"/us/usc/t19/s1677d/2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2"},"text":"(2)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" shall transfer the information (other than confidential information) concerning the practice, subsidy, or subsidy program to the library maintained under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1677f/a/1"},"text":"section 1677f(a)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":", if the practice, subsidy, or subsidy program appears to be a countervailable subsidy with respect to any other merchandise."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id05844ae6-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-17/ch497"},"text":"June 17, 1930, ch. 497","children":[],"tail":", title VII, § 775, as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/39/tI/s101"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–39, title I, § 101","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1979-07-26"},"text":"July 26, 1979","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/93/186"},"text":"93 Stat. 186","children":[],"tail":"; amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/573/tVI/s617"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–573, title VI, § 617","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1984-10-30"},"text":"Oct. 30, 1984","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/98/3037"},"text":"98 Stat. 3037","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514/tXVIII/s1886/a/12"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514, title XVIII, § 1886(a)(12)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1986-10-22"},"text":"Oct. 22, 1986","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/100/2922"},"text":"100 Stat. 2922","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/465/tII/s283/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–465, title II, § 283(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-12-08"},"text":"Dec. 8, 1994","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/108/4930"},"text":"108 Stat. 4930","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id05844ae7-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id05844ae8-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id05844ae9-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/465"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–465","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Countervailable subsidy” for “Subsidy” in section catchline and amended text generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “If, in the course of a proceeding under this subtitle, the administering authority discovers a practice which appears to be a subsidy, but was not included in the matters alleged in a countervailing duty petition, then the administering authority—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) shall include the practice in the proceeding if it appears to be a subsidy with respect to the merchandise which is the subject of the proceeding, or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) shall transfer the information concerning the practice (other than confidential information) to the library maintained under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t19/s1677f/a/1"},"text":"section 1677f(a)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":", if the practice appears to be a subsidy with respect to any other merchandise.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1986—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/514"},"text":"Pub. L. 99–514","children":[],"tail":" substituted “a proceeding” for “an proceeding” in introductory provisions."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1984—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/98/573"},"text":"Pub. L. 98–573","children":[],"tail":" substituted “proceeding” for “investigation” wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id05844aea-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d"},"text"